genresAdvancedInfo.name: marsmuziek
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A Dutch folk music genre that originated in the province of Limburg. It is characterized by the use of brass instruments, such as trumpets and trombones, and features lively melodies and upbeat rhythms. Marsmuziek is often played at festivals and celebrations, and is a staple of Dutch cultural heritage.
